reviews.text: Well worth the visit. The main house is also used for morning tea (when advertised). For a national trust building it could do with a clean and a freshen up. Bit dusty and some of the information signage is showing it's age. The garden also needs an extra bit of attention. If it's visited regularly it should be presented a bit better.
Lovely afternoon tea on the verandah despite the heat. Tasty cakes & scones on the menu.
Perfect high tea on the lawn on a dry season afternoon. All they need is the World War 2 big band soundtrack ...
A lovely piece of Darwin heritage. Must watch place if you have couple of hours.
Great. Good guides and staff

More than just a courtroom. This is an art gallery and a work of art in itself. 
ABSOLUTELY AMAZING!!!
I recommend visiting here.
Cool Building
Powerful

dopo aver visitato l'assemblea legislativa dei territori del nord,  ho visitato l'edificio della Corte Suprema,  dove  è  istallato  un bellissimo mosaico  formato da oltre 64.000 tessere  che  riproduce "il sogno della via Lattea". l'ingresso è gratuito  come per l'assemblea legislativa ma bisogna  sottoporsi agli ovvi controlli all'ingresso. Sicuramente da vedere.

Interesting Australian history and includes a lot of informational posters. However the actual tunnels themselves isn’t much to see and not worth the $7.50 (Jan 2018) entry charge. If there was some sort of guided spoken tour that concentrated on the tunnel history itself I’d rate this experience higher. With the Internet and local library you can probably read most of the information elsewhere. I left also dissatisfied I truely understood what the purpose of the tunnels were for - other than for “oil” and why the government kept them secret from the public for so long (1992).
Worth a visit when in Darwin. Lots of volunteers to help run the tunnels. Knowledgeable guides around who love to answer all your questions.
Interesting self guided tour I was only hoping the tunnels would extend a bit further.
Exhibits are well restored. A guided tour would nice.

The route is pretty straight forward which you should be able to follow and see all the information posters that explained the time line and events taken place.

Make sure you have cash and or coins preferably as is $7.50 I think and is cash only. Otherwise,  there's an commonwealth atm nearby.

The walk through towering Raintrees and unique forest palms was just the start of an adventure where around every corner there were flowering shrubs and vegetation that I had not seen anywhere else in Australia.
The birds and their melodious calls added to the experience and the African garden of mostly numerous varieties of Baobab trees was a real surprise.
Having a Cafe with outdoor seating in front of large water misting fans was a huge bonus for coffee and savouries.

We came expecting to see a botanic garden, but we didn’t expect that place would be in such bad conditions. They are apparently building and implementing few stuffs in the gardens but there is no signs or info about it. We came to see the water fall but apparently there is no or them forgot to put a sign saying it is closed.
So sad.
But if you want a place to walk into nature, see orchids is a good place though.
Good place lots to see. Very hot to walk around in the afternoon! We were told the big snake in the tree is plastic. I hope so!
Ultimate place to bring kids here, simply to have picnic. On dry season will have lots of events in this place, good for kids or family outing.
Beautiful space that is perfectly manicured and wonderful for a picnic. The cafes are great too and you know you'll always score a park. Highly recommend visiting
Nice park to visit. Lots ww2 history.  The mountain bike trails are awesome.  Good spot to get a view then big ships in the harbour.  Wear aeroguard though as lots of biting insects

Slightly overrated.
There are bunkers and lookouts are good but there are so many good lookouts around that this does not match the others.

Signage is less and beware there are lot of mosquitoes.So get your spray. I could not find any water holes. An average National Park.
Nice views of Darwin and the National Park. There are also World War 2 weapons storage bunkers. One of the bunkers has an interesting exhibition on Darwin in WW2.

Nice recreational park with BBQ's and good views over Darwin with lots of 2WW history in hidden bunkers showing examples of bombs and ammunition.
Plenty of parking and easy accessibility, but a liitle out of the way.
A fun drive with many Pokestops ! Haha it was a nice little adventure
The libary has a huge range of books but you can't borrow them. And the staff are quite loud but other than that 99% of the time it is great place for reading and studying.

I took a 1.5hour guided tour named Sara and she was great. She introduced the history, the portraits of the speakers, architecture (look out for the bomb-shaped pillars and water foundation) and pointed out where the bomb dropped and unfortunately killed 10 people in 1942. I also had a look at the parliamentary seats where there is a huge croc skin in the center of the table.

Glib guide with irritating American accent who clearly lacks knowledge of Australia, NT Parliament and political events, even those recently reported. Couldn't answer basic questions.
Replace her with someone else who has been around the NT for a while and has a real interest in the subject, for goodness sake.

Great building to visit in Darwin. It's got some amazing views and a welcoming atmosphere. It's also a centrepiece of Darwin CBD that confucts daily tours. It's not far from the waterfront restaurant district and is close to the Esplanade.
Very impressed! Beautiful building open to the public with lovely back garden outside. Cute cafe and very welcoming staff.
Its closed. No more. Stall no. 8 is salon

Ammas Cafe - the best Sri Lankan curry in the world!  And no, I am not kidding you, this woman can cook.  The depth of flavour in her curries and vegetables is out of this world.  If I could eat there everyday, I would.  There is not a lot of places in Darwin where you can get world class food, but this cafe is the exception!  Tucked away in an alley it is hard to find, and when you do find it, you will probably wonder if this little place could possibly offer you this wonderful promise of world class food?  Don't let its lack of street appeal put you off - march right in and I promise you will not regret it, and... you will be back for more!  You welcome.

This is the best Asian Fusion I've ever had. The place is always packed and has a great ambience. And you never know who you might see in this place. Whenever I'm in Darwin, a meal at Hanuman is a must for me!
This restaurant has always been great for food and service. Staff excellent. Oysters and whole fish best ever, cheese and onion naan pretty good also. JUST WISH IT WAS IN GOLD COAST ALSO

Been many times over the years while visiting Darwin. Service was good and very happy to see Rockford wines on the menu.
I must say I was a little disappointed with the food this time. Everything tasted very sweet with little to no heat. That said I still highly recommend the oysters!

Quality of the food was top class but the speed of service was poor. Staff were inattentive and failed to do basic things such as remove empty glasses from table. 45 minute wait for food and my dish came out 15 minutes after everyone else’s. Good portion sizes but very, very expensive for Indian food.
Beautiful food great service. Well priced. Always enjoy the food here

Food is good and reasonably priced. Coffee is fine.  But it's definitely better as a dry season venue if you are having lunch. Can be pretty hot during the day so make sure you snag a spot with a fan.
Nice, helpful staff. Decent beer. Okay food. Reasonable prices.

Best meal I had in Darwin. I thought ok it's a pub meal will likely be rather average but wow did they impress. I had the pork ribs with fries and coleslaw, amazing. Fast service and friendly staff. Order and bar and collect.
staff were very nice and friendly. Food was top quality, would highly recommend! Convenient location, thanks guys!

Very laid back. But good for s Saturday night.
Well done guys

This restaurant has a fantastic atmosphere, combined with elegant dining. I also really appreciated the advice that the french bartender (Allan) gave us with the cocktails selection. He was so professionally, friendly and patient with us. All the staff there helped us enjoy our night. As I'm new to Darwin, I'll definitely be back there soon to try some more of those amazing cocktails.

It’s really hard to go past this place for fine dining in Darwin. The atmosphere is quiet but refined. The air conditioning good (which is important). Importantly the food was amazing, the wine selection long and the service was prompt and regular. Highly
Recommended.

This is a classy place with good wine and a great menu. The onion sauce was sweet and delicious. Staff was informative and efficient. But service is dependent on the day. At 46$ a steak there is no room for error. I received a medium raw steak instead of a medium steak. The manager offered to replace it, but I don't waste food. No other compensation was offered. The cash register staff had no idea of what had occurred.

While I didn't get any of the fish this establishment is famous for, I still had a three course meal with wines and I wasn't overly impressed. For price vs. Quality, it doesn't justify itself enough for me. The staff are very friendly and the establishment has a lovely atmosphere. There were a few other little things that cost them a star, such as the extremely wobbly table that led to me losing a wine, and some customer service things. It isn't on my list of places to visit in Darwin.

Wow! This has been the best place I have eaten at in Darwin so far, absolutely superb. My wife and I walked in and we're greeted and seated by a very charismatic man by the name of Gavin, he was perfect. I ordered a spice rubbed rump steak and my wife a normal rump, they we're to die for! Please keep up the great work we will be back for sure! The atmosphere was lovely with the sun setting over the beach also, really clean and modern looking venue.

We had great service. Food and beverage was  excellent-presentation, amount, the way it is cooked. The whole event was catered well, no problem with the cleanliness of the toilets. We had a wonderful night.

As a regular visitor to Darwin, I have stayed in lots of hotels throughout town. But, I have now found THE ONE. This is hands down 100% credited to the absolutely immaculate condition of the lagoon pool! The beach is amazing and I have never seen any pool water so crystal clear, I was completely dumbfounded. The rooms were great too, no doubt about it. But, I will return here every time I come back mainly for the pool, it is MAGNETIC, cant stay away from it!

Sky city currently have a deal for locals. It is highly recommended. It also includes $100 to spend on drinks or in any of the Sky city reataurants. Unfortunately, the deal does not include the new wing of the complex called the Resort. It is such a great opportunity to get away without leaving Darwin. We would definitely come back again!

Loved the hotel and venue but your double standards disgusted me.  I booked a suite and showed up wearing a veterans motorcycle club t shirt, no problems at check in and you took my 500+ easy, but when I tried to exit hotel and enter casino apparently my t-shirt is not acceptable.. We are not an outlawed club and if it wasn't for veterans having once served you would not have the privilege of building a casino where you have
Casino Pretty good. Very relaxed atmosphere. Resort great clean great when you want a weekend get away and gamble.
Nice size portions. Tasty. Good service. Highly recommend. Will return

Customer service is lacking.  Food has been hit and miss lately.  They have current offers on Google for free delivery for orders over $50 or $6 delivery for orders under $50 but when I call staff aren't aware of it.  The first time they allowed me to do it.  Second time, the lady took all my details and she said she wasn't aware of the offer and she would take my order as normal and fix up before delivery. I didn't agree to that as I didn't want to be overcharged. After talking to someone she returned to again ask for my number so she could call me back, no idea when though.  I had advised she should google it and she'll see their advertisement. After 30mins I know they're not going to call back.  
Disappointing service.

Came in on Sunday 30/12/2018 from Palmerston. The website said you were open but when we got to the store it was closed. Wasted 30minutes just to drive to the store. Food is great but website needs to be better updated.
Had good time with my girlfriend at this restaurant. The menu has a good variety and the food is delicious.

Too expensive for what you're getting. Curry was extremely greasy. The menu from outside and inside was different. They charge me 1 dollor more for my beer. It was very weird. Charge what you've written on your menu. Don't trick customer!!

Such an incredible experience. Beautiful, fresh and delicious food. We took a toddler and a baby and it was still a wonderful dinner. Staff were fantastic, so accommodating and a tasty kids menu. The view is absolutely divine. Lychee martini was lovely and the tasting plate exquisite.

Fine dining in Darwin? Sounds like a mythical unicorn shooting rainbows out, BUT this is the place! Wonderful outdoor settings and spot on service. If you’re looking for quality over quantity this is the place.
Fantastic views, great staff that were friendly and efficient. The food was delicious....a nice place for a nice dinner

Really impressed with the food and the genuine service my first night out at Pee Wee’s. As soon as I had my entree scallops I knew I was in food heaven. Good portions with impeccable flavours  thoughtfully paired together. I’m a huge foodie and although a bit pricey, was worth every dollar. Many thanks to our wonderful waiter Max, very professional, passionate and knowledgeable. Looking forward to next meal and experience.

Amazing food and great atmosphere. The tables are right by the water and spaced far apart so it feels like you are dining on your own more, which is lovely. The share platter for your entree is highly recommended.

We had great service. Food and beverage was  excellent-presentation, amount, the way it is cooked. The whole event was catered well, no problem with the cleanliness of the toilets. We had a wonderful night.
